---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import HomeHeroImage from '../assets/1.png';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<Image src={HomeHeroImage} alt="Prompt and Circumstance Blog" />
			<h1>Welcome to Prompt and Circumstance</h1>
			<p>
				Hey there! I'm <strong>Aadhavan</strong>, a computer science student passionate about the intersection of technology and finance. This blog is where I explore the fascinating world of <strong>Large Language Models</strong>, <strong>Machine Learning</strong>, <strong>Data Science</strong>, and <strong>Financial Risk Management</strong>.
			</p>
			<p>
				Currently diving deep into both the technical and theoretical aspects of AI while preparing for the <strong>Financial Risk Manager (FRM)</strong> exam. You'll find insights on everything from transformer architectures and multimodal AI to quantitative finance and risk modeling.
			</p>
			<h2>What You'll Find Here</h2>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>LLM Deep Dives</strong> - Exploring text and image models, their architectures, and applications</li>
				<li><strong>ML/DS Tutorials</strong> - Practical guides and theoretical insights in machine learning and data science</li>
				<li><strong>Finance & Risk</strong> - Quantitative finance, risk management, and fintech innovations</li>
				<li><strong>Student Perspectives</strong> - Learning journey insights and academic project breakdowns</li>
			</ul>
			<p>
				Whether you're a fellow student, researcher, or practitioner in these fields, I hope you find something valuable here. Let's explore the prompts and circumstances that shape our AI-driven future together.
			</p>
			<p>
				<a href="/blog">Start reading â†’</a>
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
